-- India-Australia One-Day Match Is Abandoned Because of Rain in Kochi
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2010-10-17T11:21:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-17/india-australia-one-day-match-is-abandoned-because-of-rain-in-kochi.html
The opening one-day cricket
international between India and Australia in Kochi was abandoned
today without a ball being bowled because of rain.  The second match of three-game series is scheduled for Oct.
20 in Visakhapatnam, with the final fixture in Goa four days
later.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  